events.text:
Day of Doubt
The stars are beautiful, but I can’t help but wonder when I last went to the bathroom.
I can’t recall a single instance of defecation in all my time here.
In fact, I don’t remember ever taking this suit off.
I don’t know how.
Where does the suit end and I begin?
For that matter, where do the moon carrots go?
I “eat” them in the sense that after I collect them, I feel a sense of fullness, but I do not put them into my mouth.
Do I even have one?
How would I know?
I can’t take this damn helmet off.
As the moon bunny continues to expand and consume more and more moon carrots, I can’t help but wonder where they go as well.
There are no artificial hills on the moon courtesy of the moon bunny, and I have yet to see it since I sent it out the airlock.
Perhaps the extraordinary growth of the creature can be attributed to the mass of the moon carrots.
If they are not broken down inside the body, are they still there rolling around inside the moon bunny’s cavernous stomach?
Is the moon bunny simply a mass of veg with fluffy cheeks?
I had best be careful around its mouth.
